              "Description": "Prevention Program Description:\n\nThe prevention program is comprised of employee training, system reviews and inspections, as well as a facility wide emergency response plan.  The employee training program includes a general awareness of the hazards and emergency response plan related to chlorine.  Employees that work with the processes receive more specific training related to maintenance, inspections, operation, and safety of the processes.  Awareness and emergency action information is provided to contractors working on or near the chlorine processes.\n\nThe mechanical integrity program involves periodic inspections of the chlorine process equipment and operations.  The emergency action plan covers the chlorine processes and is organized to mitigate potential releases and protect the safety of employees and the public.  \n\nThe combination of training, frequent inspections, and an established emergency action plan has resulted in a system that operates in a safe and efficient manner.  In addition, the plant adheres to the OSHA Process Safety Management program, which adds additional safety and awareness to the chlorine process.",
